request.description:
Employees can flag a gif.

<h3>Request spec: (header)</h3>
{
	"token": "string"
}

<h3>Request spec: (header)</h3>
{
	"flag": "true" or "false" for only admin
}

<h3>Response spec: </h3>
{
	"status": "success"
	"data": {
		message: "Gif flagged successfully"
		or
		"message": "Gif successfully unflagged" for only admin
	}
}

Employees can flag a comment on a gif post.

<h3>Request spec: (header)</h3>
{
	"token": "string"
}

<h3>Request spec: (header)</h3>
{
	"flag": "true" or "false" for only admin
}

<h3>Response spec: </h3>
{
	"status": "success"
	"data": {
		"message": "Comment flagged successfully"
		or
		"message": "Comment successfully unflagged" for only admin
	}
}

Employees can delete their articles.

<h3>Request spec: (Header)</h3>
{
	“token”: String,
	...
}

<h3>Response spec:</h3>
{
	“status” : “success”,
	“data” : {
		“message”: “gif post successfully deleted”,
		...
	}
}

Employees can comment on other colleagues' gif post.

<h3>Request spec: (Header)</h3>
{
	“token”: String,
	...
}

<h3>Request spec: (body)</h3>
{
	“comment”: String,
	...
}

<h3>Response spec:</h3>
{
	“status” : “success”,
	“data” : {
		“message”: “comment successfully created”,
		“createdOn”: DateTime,
		“gifTitle”: String,
		“comment”: String,
		...
	}
}

response.body:
{
    "status": "success",
    "data": {
        "message": "Comment successfully created",
        "createdOn": "11/22/2019",
        "gifTitle": "hsv color",
        "comment": "You've got a scaled form of the image. Cool!"
    }
}

request.description:
Employees can view a specific gif post.

<h3>Request spec: (Header)</h3>
{
	“token”: String,
	...
}

<h3>Response spec:</h3>
{
	“status” : “success”,
	“data” : {
		“id”: Integer,
		“createdOn”: DateTime,
		“title”: String,
		“url”: String,
		“comments”: [
			{
				“commentId”: Integer,
				“authorId”: Integer,
				“comment”: String,
			},
			{
				“commentId”: Integer,
				“useauthorIdrId”: Integer,
				“comment”: String,
			}
		]
	}
}

